From 7dd6e9750eb47fdd319ab7deaf28eb22c5d17cf1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jayanth Othayoth <Jayanth.Othayoth@amd.com>
Date: Sat, 21 Jun 2025 10:24:53 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] RDE: Add Device and Manager interfaces

Introduces new D-Bus interfaces to support Redfish Device Enablement
capabilities in OpenBMC. Adds per-device introspection via the
xyz.openbmc_project.RDE.Device interface and a centralized control path
via xyz.openbmc_project.RDE.Manager.

The Device interface exposes supported operations, features,
schema descriptors, and capability negotiation status for each
discovered device.

The Manager interface supports performing Redfish operations
(GET, POST,etc.) on target devices using inline or file-based
payloads with optional encoding hints.

Key additions:
  - OperationType, FeatureType, and SchemaDescriptorKeys enums.
  - PerformRedfishOperation, GetDeviceSchemaInfo, and
    GetSupportedOperations  methods.
  - Support for PayloadFormatType and SchemaOutputFormat for
    flexible input and output handling.
  - NegotiationStatus enum tracks RDE capability negotiation state.

Upstream Status: [Review https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/phosphor-dbus-interfaces/+/81300]

Signed-off-by: Jayanth Othayoth <Jayanth.Othayoth@amd.com>
